od to everyone.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nTo be a woman is to be a fighter! A woman has to be strong and has to fight every moment of her life - against a society that believes in patriarchy, chauvinism and male privilege!\n\n- Avijeet\n|\nFor peace read books, for success read books and take actions.\n\n- Amit\n|\nLife is a practice. When you 'fail,' you can immediately begin practicing again.\n\n- Bryant McGill, Simple Reminders: Inspiration for Living Your Best Life\n|\nShe thinks of her mother, sitting cross-legged, sewing marigolds into garlands for the gods, telling her: 'The biggest mistake we make is thinking we are powerless\n\n- Isha\n|\nBefore getting upset, always ask yourself: Will this even matter in six months, in a year, or in five years? if the answer is no, then let it go.\n\n- Robin\n|\nWe do have the ability to manifest things, but our purpose, our end, our legacy is alsocontrolled by our destiny. So focus on what comes easy—that is your destined life.\n\n- Emma Mildon, The Soul Searcher's Handbook: A Modern Girl's Guide to the New Age World\n|\nI'd always had a guilty preference for fiction. Since I seemed now to be living fiction, this proved to have been an entirely reasonable choice.\n\n- Robin McKinley, Sunshine\n|\nWeird is my personality, Complicated are my words and Mystery I am but those what gets you to like me.\n\n- Red\n|\nHe didn't blame James for falling in love with her, she was a radiant, deserving woman. He knew, however, that love only did one thing. It got in the way.\n\n- Erin M. Truesdale, Breaking Away\n|\nIf this continues, if this goes on, then when I die, your memories of me will be my greatest accomplishment. You memories will be my most lasting impressions.\n\n- David Levithan, The Lover's Dictionary\n|\nWith a strong faith in God and confidence in your abilities, who can dare to stop you?\n\n- Unknown\n|\nRalph Waldo Emerson“Do not go where the path may lead, go instead where there is no path and leave a trail.”― Ralph Waldo Emerson\n\n- Ralph\n|\nI confess, I do not believe in time.\n\n- Vladimir\n|\nModern medical advances have helped millions of people live longer, healthier lives. We owe these improvements to decades of investment in medical research.\n\n- Ike\n|\nNext to the love of God, the love of country is the best preventive of crime.\n\n- George\n|\nThere are big advantages of living for God, therefore try to spend every minute you have walking with Him, listening to Him and learning of His wisdom\n\n- Sunday\n|\nBelieve in yourself, Follow your dreams, and all things are possible!\n\n- Garry\n|\nGood enough may be an acceptable end, but it should never be an acceptable goal.\n\n- James\n|\nThere was something of Francis in the boy, something pure and genuine and flawed. That type didn't think twice before running headlong into a burning house or a young girl's arms.\n\n- Johanna Moran, The Wives of Henry Oades\n|\nThe curse of the romantic is a greed for dreams, an intensity of expectation that, in the end, diminishes the reality.\n\n- Marya\n|\nIf you're going to buy a castle, make sure you get on the property extension ladder.\n\n- Benny Bellamacina, Philosophical Uplifting Quotes volume 2\n|\nI knew that (job) had to be a humbling role for my dad, but he never allowed it to become humiliating work.\n\n- Jeremy Camp, I Still Believe\n|\nEmbracing change can be daunting, but it is our willingness to do better that makes it worthwhile.\n\n- Peprah\n|\nA true leader leads for the sake of love and his knowledge of the path, a bad leader redirects his followers to the path of destruction.\n\n- Michael\n|\nNakajima’s past would always be there, so the foundation could crumble at any moment. That’s what happens, I realized, when people destroy other people.\n\n- Banana Yoshimoto, The Lake\n|\nFor he who lives as passion directs will not hear argument that dissuades him, nor understand it if he does; and how can we persuade one in such a state to change his ways?\n\n- Aristotle, Th