at is obtained from the temporary.\n\n- Dada\n|\nAll power tends to coopt, and absolute power coopts absolutely.\n\n- Alasdair MacIntyre, After Virtue: A Study in Moral Theory\n|\nThere is no doubt that creativity is the most important human resource of all. Without creativity, there would be no progress, and we would be forever repeating the same patterns.\n\n- Edward\n|\nTalking about unpleasant things during a meal is not good for digestion, not good for health.\n\n- Betty\n|\nThis is what I miss, Cordelia: not something that’s gone, but something that will never happen. Two old women giggling over their tea.\n\n- Margaret Atwood, Cat's Eye\n|\nMisunderstanding arising from ignorance breeds fear, and fear remains the greatest enemy of peace.\n\n- Lester\n|\nIf some great catastrophe is not announced every morning, we feel a certain void. Nothing in the paper today, we sigh.\n\n- Lord\n|\nWhen I hear somebody sigh, 'Life is hard,' I am always tempted to ask, 'Compared to what?'\n\n- Sydney\n|\nIf you lined up 10 writers and asked them to write a movie about Steve Jobs, you'd get 10 very different movies.\n\n- Aaron\n|\nEach of us has his own inner concentration camp... We must deal with, with forgiveness and patience-as full human beings, as we are and what we will become.\n\n- Viktor\n|\nOne can have a wit, but not a witless\n\n- Brandon Sanderson, The Way of Kings\n|\nSometimes you have to walk through the fire, in order to reach your calling.\n\n- Shannon\n|\nI think we all keep irritating situations in our head to long, until we finally realize it’s taking up valuable space.\n\n- Ron\n|\nIntelligence is an accident of evolution, and not necessarily an advantage.\n\n- Isaac\n|\nWe are not defined by the things we accumulate, but by the memories we impart.\n\n- Philip\n|\nDear God. She ached, wanting something that she knew was a sin.Wanting a man who was sin itself.\n\n- Elizabeth Hoyt, Scandalous Desires\n|\nThe answer must be, I think, that the beauty and grace are performed whether or not we will or sense them. The least we can do is try to be there.\n\n- Annie Dillard, Pilgrim at Tinker Creek\n|\nTheres something alluring and dangerous about him, but comforting and protective. When I think about him, my stomach knots, my heart rate quickens and...and I could go on... -Laney\n\n- Joann I. Martin Sowles, Laney\n|\nThat Science thing 'For every action there is an equal and opposite reaction' Well this is not true if you hit someone much bigger then you.\n\n- Chuck\n|\nWhen you're young you think you know it all, when you're old you wish you could remember it all.\n\n- T.A.\n|\nHe was all of those things, of course, but none of those things.\n\n- Marie Tillman, The Letter: My Journey Through Love, Loss, and Life\n|\nThe sad thing about any business I suppose, but in mine you see it particularly, is that you're always asked to do what you've already done.\n\n- Jeremy\n|\nAnd reading itself is an amazing activity: You glance at a thin, flat object made from a tree...and the voice of the author begins to speak inside your head. (Hello!)\n\n- Carl Sagan, Dragons of Eden: Speculations on the Evolution of Human Intelligence\n|\nThey are simple people, most of them, but that doesn't make them subhuman.You are telling them Jesus loves them, but not much.\n\n- Harper\n|\nIf you actually are an educated, thinking person, you will not be welcome in Washington, D.C. I know a couple of bright seventh graders who would not be welcome in Washington D.C.\n\n- Kurt Vonnegut Jr., A Man Without a Country\n|\nAccept changes in others, as much as you would want them to accept changes in you.\n\n- Innocent Mwatsikesimbe, Mirror\n|\nWho is the most worthy of admiration, musician or audience?Probably the musician will tell that his audience and the musician that his audience\n\n- Válgame, Zori 2ª Parte\n|\nAnd finally, always remember that the other person started it.\n\n- Brandi Glanville, Drinking and Tweeting and Other Brandi Blunders\n|\nPowerful to alleviate, to delay, to camouflage, though money is, in the end it lets us down.\n\n- Caryll Houselander, The Reed of God\n|\nThe truth is that everything contains everything else. We cannot just be, we can only inter-be.\n\n- Thich Nhat Hanh, Peace Is Every Step: The Path of Mindfulness in Everyday Life\n|\nEveryone will not favor you or respect your beliefs, passion and purpose--so be it. But do not allow the views of others to hinder your quest. Remain steadfast.\n\n- Terry\n|\nThe instinct, quiet inner voice is the voice of the Holy Spirit.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!"